div.p: url-shortener-m3 Handler URLService PostgreSQL
Legend Happy path Error path Retry loop Red border = same DB transaction Dashed arrow = error branch Solid arrow = success flow

Validate JWT Extract Claims IN: Authorization: Bearer <token> header ACTION: RequireAuth middleware calls JWTVerifier.Verify(token) Local HMAC-SHA256 no network call Extract: claims.Sub user_id (UUID) Extract: claims.Email user_email OUT: (user_id: string, user_email: string)
401 {"error":"unauthorized"} ErrTokenExpired 401 ErrTokenInvalid 401 Missing header 401

Validate URL + Parse Request Body IN: ShortenRequest{url, custom_code?, expires_at?} Body limit: http.MaxBytesReader(w, r.Body, 4096) ACTION: url.Parse(req.URL) Go stdlib Require: parsed.Scheme {http, https} Require: parsed.Host != "" If expires_at present: time.Parse(RFC3339, *req.ExpiresAt) Require: expiresAt.After(time.Now()) OUT: (originalURL: string, expiresAt: *time.Time, customCode: string)

400 Missing scheme/host "url must include scheme and host" Non-http scheme "url scheme must be http or https" Bad expires_at "expires_at must be RFC3339 format" Past expires_at "expires_at must be in the future" Body > 4096B "request body too large"

Select Short Code (with Collision Retry) IN: customCode: string (may be empty) BRANCH A Custom Code Provided: Validate: len [4,10], all chars in base62Alphabet Use as-is collision detected at DB INSERT (Step ) Custom code conflict 409 (not retried) BRANCH B Auto-Generate (loop 5 attempts):
go for attempt := 1; attempt <= 5; attempt++ { code = codegen.Generate() // crypto/rand, 7 chars attempt INSERT (Step ) if ErrCodeConflict: continue // retry if success: break }
if attempt > 5: return ErrExhausted 503
base62Alphabet = "0123456789A-Za-z" (62 chars) Collision space: 62 3.5 trillion codes OUT: shortCode: string (7 chars auto / 4-10 chars custom)
503 5 collision retries exhausted {"error":"could not generate unique code; try again"} (Indicates pathologically high collision rate)

BEGIN PostgreSQL Transaction IN: *pgxpool.Pool ACTION: tx, err = pool.Begin(ctx) defer tx.Rollback(ctx) auto-rollback if Commit not reached OUT: pgx.Tx transaction handle passed to Steps and Both Steps and MUST use this same tx No HTTP response before COMMIT succeeds

g.text: ATOMIC TRANSACTION Steps + execute in same pgx.Tx

div.p: COMMIT Transaction IN: Open pgx.Tx with both rows written (uncommitted) ACTION: err = tx.Commit(ctx) On success:

ul.li: urls row is durable and visible to other connections

outbox row is durable and visible to poller goroutine CRASH BETWEEN COMMIT AND HTTP RESPONSE: Client receives connection reset URL WAS created Client may retry second INSERT hits unique constraint 409 OUT: Both rows committed; transaction closed

div.p: 500 Commit fails (extremely rare: network partition to DB) Both rows rolled back atomically {"error":"internal server error"}
HTTP 201 Created Response Body: json { "short_code": "aB3xY9z", "short_url": "http://localhost:8081/aB3xY9z", "original_url": "https://very-long-url.example.com/path", "expires_at": null }
Collision Retry Loop ErrCodeConflict from Step (auto-code only) causes control to return to Step to generate a new 7-char code.
Outbox Poller (url-service, 3 workers) Polls every 2s: SELECT id FROM outbox WHERE published_at IS NULL Publishes to RabbitMQ routing key: url.created
ATOMICITY INVARIANT: Both INSERTs succeed or both roll back. A URL row can never exist without its outbox row. An outbox row can never exist for a URL that was not created.

INSERT INTO urls (within tx) IN: (tx, URL{id, short_code, original_url, user_id, expires_at}) url.ID = uuid.New().String() generated by app, not DB SQL: sql INSERT INTO urls (id, short_code, original_url, user_id, expires_at) VALUES ($1, $2, $3, $4, $5)

Unique index idx_urls_short_code enforces collision detection. ON 23505 (unique violation): ErrCodeConflict returned to Shorten() tx rolled back by defer if auto-code: retry loop at Step if custom-code: 409 immediately OUT: URL row in DB (uncommitted until Step )

INSERT INTO outbox (within same tx) IN: (tx, eventType="url.created", payload=URLCreatedEvent JSON) URLCreatedEvent payload: json { "event_type": "url.created", "occurred_at": "2026-03-02T14:00:00Z", "correlation_id": "UUID-FROM-HEADER", "short_code": "aB3xY9z", "original_url": "https://...", "user_id": "JWT-SUB", "user_email": "JWT-EMAIL", "expires_at": null }
SQL: sql INSERT INTO outbox (id, event_type, payload, created_at) VALUES (gen_random_uuid(), $1, $2, now())
published_at starts NULL poller picks it up OUT: Outbox row in DB (uncommitted until Step )
Rollback (defer) 23505 ErrCodeConflict retry if auto-code 409 if custom-code Other DB error 500
Rollback (defer) Outbox INSERT fails 500 urls row also rolled back No partial state possible
